<div style="text-align:justify">

  <h3 id="cencoos-partnership-ocean-information-for-decision-makers-cencoos-data-management-services-"><b> CeNCOOS Partnership: Ocean Information for Decision Makers: CeNCOOS Data Management Services </b></h3>

  <h4 id="closing-observational-gaps-in-the-california-current-system-the-point-arena-underwater-glider-line-"><b> Closing observational gaps in the California Current System: the Point Arena Underwater Glider Line </b></h4>

  <p>CeNCOOS Partnership: Ocean Information for Decision Makers: CeNCOOS Data
Management Services. NOAA IOOS. $106,000. (06/01/2019 - 05/31/2020). co-PI.
(Lead-PI: Henry Ruhl - MBARI).</p>

  <p>Funded by <strong>NATIONAL SCIENCE FOUNDATION <a href="https://www.nsf.gov/index.jsp"> (NSF) </a></strong>. <br /></p>

  <p><strong>LEAD-PI</strong>: Dr. Henry Ruhl (MBARI) <br />
<strong>CO-PIs</strong>: Dr. Piero Mazzini (VIMS)  and Dr. Karina Nielsen (SFSU). <br /></p>

  <p>Period: June, 2020 to May 31, 2023. <br /></p>

  <p>A new underwater glider line has been implemented beginning in Dec-2019, located off Point Arena, northern California. This new line is part of the Central and Northern California Ocean Observing System - CeNCOOS (<a href="https://www.cencoos.org/">https://www.cencoos.org</a>), and is being coordinated by Dr. Mazzini in collaboration with Dr. Dan Rudnick (UCSD SIO), Dr. Henry Ruhl (CeNCOOS/MBARI), Dr. John Largier (UC Davis), Dr. Jack Barth (OSU), Dr. Francisco Chaves (MBARI), and many others. This line will help monitor changes of the ocean physics and biochemistry, helping to advance our knowledge of the California Current System and improve ocean model forecast in the region.</p>

  <p> Real time data can be obtained at: <a href="https://www.cencoos.org/data/gliders/line56_7">https://www.cencoos.org/data/gliders/line56_7</a> </p>

</div>

